<TITLE> Brave the floods with high spirits: Moeen </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sirajganj, Aug 19 (bdnews24.com)The army chief, General Moeen U Ahmed, has said the government is thinking of building a permanent flood embankment at Kazipur in Sirajganj district. The army chief also said floods were an unavoidable natural calamity that the country must face with strong spirits. "Everybody must work with renewed spirits. Houses must be repaired, and crops grown before winter," said Moeen, speaking to flood victims and distributing relief materials in Kazipur Sunday. He encouraged those in need to visit treatment facilities in the mobile hospitals of the army. The army chief arrived in Kazipur upazila by helicopter to distribute seeds among flood-affected farmers. He went on to Meghai Bazaar by foot to give out clothing and milk powder to the needy families. After the relief operation, he visited a 30-bed mobile hospital run by the army in Meghai Bazaar and enquired after patients. bdnews24
